	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />A lot of us were confused because payment cards in the United States tend to have no annual fee. Some high-end credit cards with certain kinds of rewards have an annual fee, but ordinary credit cards make money for the bank on finance charges (i.e. interest). Debit cards sold as "gift cards" have an issue fee, but debit cards linked to a checking account or (in some countries) a PayPal account make money on loans that the bank makes using the money in the account. And both kinds of cards make money on the merchant fee.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


