		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">If your debit card has embossed numbers on the front and says "VISA" or "MasterCard" then it should work for any merchant that takes VISA or MasterCard cards.</div>
<br />Right, my debit card is a VISA card, so I can use it anywhere. It just doesn't have any credit attached to it, so I can't spend money I don't have.
<br />
<br />Although I try to use my physical card only when I need to. For online purchases I use a service from my bank called "e-card". It's an application that generates virtual VISA cards where you can specify the maximum amount that can be charged on the card (ever), as well as how many months the card should be valid.
<br />It's a feature I definitely wouldn't want to be without.

		

