		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">ReaperSMS wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I believe the "cash discount" approach in the US tends to get retailers in trouble with Visa/MC as it's a violation of the merchant agreement.</div>
<br />It's not if they post the cash discounted prices alongside <em>every</em> normal price. So if a store has price tags on everything, these would have to list both prices. The main thing they really can't do is have a surcharge for cards; any price difference must be framed as a discount. Apparently buyers prefer not to have cash discounts, because they believe it implies higher prices and thus shop in places that lack the discount. I love my country.

		

		</td>
